<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB03523</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT CREATING THE COCONUT INDUSTRY TRUST FUND, PROVIDING FOR ITS MANAGEMENT AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Coconut Industry Trust Fund Act</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to constitute the coconut levy funds and assets in a Coconut Industry Trust Fund and provide the administrative structure that will manage the trust funds and ensure that its use will benefit the coconut industry and the coconut farmers.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>PINEDA, ENRICO A., ROMERO, MICHAEL ODYLON L., Ph.D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-09-07</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Economic</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Scheduled for meeting/hearing on 2016-10-18</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-A Technical Working Group was created to further study the proposed measure together with other Coco Levy Fund bills. The Committee agreed to use HB 6135, the Coconut Farmers and Industry Development Act, as approved in the 16th Congress, as reference bill.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Under study by the Technical Working Group(TWG) on 2016-11-10</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-The Technical Working Group meeting was attended by all sectors which includes small coconut farmers organizations, concerned government agencies and other industry stakeholders. A second TWG meeting was scheduled to continue the deliberation on the proposed measure</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp3. Scheduled for meeting/hearing on 2017-05-23</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp4. Approved by the Committee on Appropriations on 2017-05-23</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Substitute Bill to House Bill Nos. 62, 102, 164, 301, 557, 2175, 2266, 2749, 2833, 2840, 3523, 4089, 4224, 4286, 4632 and 4803 was approved with amendments.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB05745</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE AND FOOD ON 2016-09-14</td></tr></table>